== Dependencies

- camping
	- markaby
	- metaid

- stdlib
	- net/imap
	- net/smtp
	- yaml

- ruby-dbi
	- dbd-sqlite3

== Features

- Manipulating messages:
	- Read (including attachments)
	- Move to folders
	- Delete

== Setup

mailbox.conf contains values to configure Camping at the Mailbox.

Among them are imaphost and smtphost, both of which can use the token
%{domain}, which will be replaced by the domain in a username.

imapport and smtpport can be used to change which ports are connected to. 
Ruby's Net::IMAP module will use SSL on port 993 for IMAP

You can make a file 'banner', which will be displayed on the login screen.
